{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":824,"text":"I'd like for you to take a moment\nto imagine this with me."},{"time":6144,"text":"You're a little girl of five years old."},{"time":10069,"text":"Sitting in front of a mirror,"},{"time":11822,"text":"you ask yourself,"},{"time":14395,"text":"\"Do I exist?\""},{"time":17254,"text":"In this space, there is\nvery little context,"},{"time":19930,"text":"and so you move into a different one,"},{"time":22518,"text":"one filled with people."},{"time":25124,"text":"Surely, now you know you're not\na figment of your own imagination."},{"time":29223,"text":"You breathe their air."},{"time":31385,"text":"You see them,"},{"time":32839,"text":"so they must see you."},{"time":35348,"text":"And yet, you still can't help but wonder:"},{"time":40480,"text":"Do I only exist when people speak to me?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":45796,"text":"Pretty heavy thoughts for a child, right?"},{"time":49001,"text":"But through various artworks\nthat reflect upon our society,"},{"time":53533,"text":"I came to understand\nhow a young black girl can grow up"},{"time":57707,"text":"feeling as if she's not seen,\nand perhaps she doesn't exist."},{"time":64337,"text":"You see, if young people don't have\npositive images of themselves"},{"time":68130,"text":"and all that remains\nare negative stereotypes,"},{"time":71322,"text":"this affects their self-image."},{"time":74214,"text":"But it also affects the way\nthat the rest of society treats them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":79282,"text":"I discovered this"},{"time":80542,"text":"having lived in Cape Town\nfor about five years at the time."},{"time":85114,"text":"I felt a deep sense\nof dislocation and invisibility."},{"time":91322,"text":"I couldn't see myself represented."},{"time":94361,"text":"I couldn't see the women who've raised me,"},{"time":97240,"text":"the ones who've influenced me,"},{"time":99126,"text":"and the ones that have made\nSouth Africa what it is today."},{"time":102889,"text":"I decided to do something about it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":107125,"text":"What do you think when you see this?"},{"time":111751,"text":"If you were a black girl,"},{"time":113896,"text":"how would it make you feel?"},{"time":117273,"text":"Walking down the street,"},{"time":119742,"text":"what does the city you live in say to you?"},{"time":123626,"text":"What symbols are present?"},{"time":125550,"text":"Which histories are celebrated?"},{"time":128059,"text":"And on the other hand,"},{"time":129309,"text":"which ones are omitted?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":131703,"text":"You see, public spaces are hardly\never as neutral as they may seem."},{"time":136452,"text":"I discovered this when I made\nthis performance in 2013 on Heritage Day."},{"time":144272,"text":"Cape Town is teeming\nwith masculine architecture,"},{"time":149431,"text":"monuments and statues,"},{"time":151514,"text":"such as Louis Botha in that photograph."},{"time":154836,"text":"This overt presence of white colonial\nand Afrikaner nationalist men"},{"time":160776,"text":"not only echoes a social,\ngender and racial divide,"},{"time":166927,"text":"but it also continues to affect\nthe way that women --"},{"time":171577,"text":"and the way, particularly, black women --"},{"time":174801,"text":"see themselves in relation\nto dominant male figures"},{"time":180236,"text":"in public spaces."},{"time":185076,"text":"For this reason, among others,"},{"time":187392,"text":"I don't believe that we need statues."},{"time":190506,"text":"The preservation of history\nand the act of remembering"},{"time":194416,"text":"can be achieved in more memorable\nand effective ways."}]},{"cues":[{"time":200424,"text":"As part of a year-long\npublic holiday series,"},{"time":204307,"text":"I use performance art\nas a form of social commentary"},{"time":208458,"text":"to draw people's attention\nto certain issues,"},{"time":211680,"text":"as well as addressing the absence\nof the black female body"},{"time":217654,"text":"in memorialized public spaces,"},{"time":219916,"text":"especially on public holidays."},{"time":223155,"text":"Women's Day was coming up."},{"time":225269,"text":"I looked at what the day means --"},{"time":227960,"text":"the Women's March\nto the union buildings in 1956,"},{"time":232639,"text":"petitioning against the pass laws."},{"time":236070,"text":"Juxtaposed with the hypocrisy\nof how women are treated,"},{"time":240900,"text":"especially in public spaces today,"},{"time":243980,"text":"I decided to do something about it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":247337,"text":"Headline:"}]},{"cues":[{"time":249017,"text":"[Women in miniskirt attacked at taxi rank]"}]},{"cues":[{"time":257009,"text":"How do I comment on such polar opposites?"},{"time":261737,"text":"In the guise of my great-grandmother,"},{"time":263902,"text":"I performed bare-breasted,"},{"time":265629,"text":"close to the taxi rank in KwaLanga."},{"time":269326,"text":"This space is also called Freedom Square,"},{"time":271931,"text":"where women were a part of demonstrations\nagainst apartheid laws."},{"time":277156,"text":"I was not comfortable with women\nbeing seen as only victims in society."},{"time":284539,"text":"You might wonder\nhow people reacted to this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":287931,"text":"(Video) Woman: (Cheering)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":291366,"text":"Woman 2 (offscreen): Yes!"}]},{"cues":[{"time":301054,"text":"Sethembile Msezane: Pretty cool, huh?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":304134,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":307882,"text":"So I realized that through\nmy performances,"},{"time":310860,"text":"I've been able to make regular people\nreflect upon their society,"},{"time":315968,"text":"looking at the past\nas well as the current democracy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":319692,"text":"(Video) Man (offscreen):\nShe's been there since three o'clock."}]},{"cues":[{"time":322673,"text":"Man 2 (offscreen): Just before three.\nAbout an hour still?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":325431,"text":"Man 1: Yeah. It's just a really hot day."}]},{"cues":[{"time":333711,"text":"Man 1: It's very interesting."},{"time":335719,"text":"It's very powerful."},{"time":338324,"text":"I think it's cool."},{"time":342643,"text":"I think a lot of people\nare quick to join a group"},{"time":347992,"text":"that's a movement towards something,"},{"time":349888,"text":"but not many people are ready\nto do something as an individual."}]},{"cues":[{"time":355139,"text":"Man 2: So it's the individual\nversus the collective."}]},{"cues":[{"time":357770,"text":"Man 1: Yeah."},{"time":358950,"text":"So I think her pushing her own\nindividual message in performance ..."},{"time":365920,"text":"it's powerful."},{"time":368185,"text":"Yeah, I think it's quite powerful\nthat she's doing it on her own."},{"time":373466,"text":"I'd be interested to know why\nshe's using hair extensions as wings,"},{"time":377631,"text":"or whatever those things are meant to be."},{"time":382874,"text":"They are wings, yes?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":386754,"text":"Woman 3: With her standing\nthere right now,"},{"time":389044,"text":"I think it's just my interpretation"},{"time":393028,"text":"that we are bringing the statue down"},{"time":396423,"text":"and bringing up something"},{"time":398672,"text":"that's supposed to represent\nAfrican pride, I think."},{"time":403301,"text":"Or something like that."},{"time":405801,"text":"Something should stand while Rhodes falls,"},{"time":409301,"text":"I think that's what it's saying. Yeah."},{"time":412748,"text":"Yes. Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":413988,"text":"Man 3: What is behind me\nrepresents the African culture."},{"time":417475,"text":"We can't have the colonialist law,"},{"time":419888,"text":"so we need to remove\nall these colonial statues."},{"time":422803,"text":"We have have our own statues now,"},{"time":425321,"text":"our African leaders --\nBhambatha, Moshoeshoe, Kwame Nkrumah --"},{"time":430217,"text":"all those who paid their lives\nfor our liberation."},{"time":434474,"text":"We can't continue in the 21st century,"},{"time":436806,"text":"and after 21 years of democracy,"},{"time":438867,"text":"have the colonizers in our own country."},{"time":441031,"text":"They belong somewhere.\nMaybe in a museum; not here."},{"time":444028,"text":"I mean learning institutions,\nplaces where young people,"},{"time":447202,"text":"young minds are being shaped."},{"time":448804,"text":"So we cannot continue to have Louis Botha,\nRhodes, all these people,"},{"time":453518,"text":"because they're representing\nthe colonialism."}]},{"cues":[{"time":458699,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":464015,"text":"Sethembile Msezane: On April 9, 2015,"},{"time":467062,"text":"the Cecil John Rhodes statue\nwas scheduled to be removed"},{"time":471063,"text":"after a month of debates\nfor and against its removal"},{"time":475302,"text":"by various stakeholders."},{"time":478614,"text":"This caused a widespread interest\nin statues in South Africa."},{"time":483211,"text":"Opinions varied, but the media\nfocused on problematizing"},{"time":488566,"text":"the removal of statues."},{"time":493092,"text":"On that -- well, that year,\nI had just begun my master's"},{"time":496951,"text":"at the University of Cape Town."},{"time":500245,"text":"During the time\nof the debate of the statue,"},{"time":503659,"text":"I had been having reoccurring dreams"},{"time":507593,"text":"about a bird."},{"time":509497,"text":"And so I started conjuring her"},{"time":512199,"text":"mentally, spiritually and through dress."},{"time":518052,"text":"On that day,"},{"time":519769,"text":"I happened to be having\na meeting with my supervisors,"},{"time":523429,"text":"and they told me that the statue\nwas going to fall on that day."},{"time":528105,"text":"I told them that I'd explain later,"},{"time":530548,"text":"but we had to postpone the meeting"},{"time":532510,"text":"because I was going to perform her\nas the statue came down."}]},{"cues":[{"time":537532,"text":"Her name was Chapungu."},{"time":539436,"text":"She was a soapstone bird\nthat was looted from Great Zimbabwe"},{"time":543840,"text":"in the late 1800s,"},{"time":545612,"text":"and is still currently housed\nin Cecil John Rhodes's estate"},{"time":549669,"text":"in Cape Town."},{"time":552104,"text":"On that day,"},{"time":553304,"text":"I embodied her existence using my body,"},{"time":557438,"text":"while standing in the blazing sun\nfor nearly four hours."},{"time":563246,"text":"As the time came,"},{"time":565114,"text":"the crane came alive."},{"time":567201,"text":"The people did, too --"},{"time":569002,"text":"shouting,"},{"time":570185,"text":"screaming,"},{"time":571446,"text":"clenching their fists"},{"time":573380,"text":"and taking pictures of the moment\non their phones and cameras."},{"time":577939,"text":"Chapungu's wings,"},{"time":579482,"text":"along with the crane,"},{"time":580905,"text":"rose to declare the fall\nof Cecil John Rhodes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":587143,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":592192,"text":"Euphoria filled the air\nas he became absent from his base,"},{"time":596809,"text":"while she remained still,"},{"time":600191,"text":"very present,"},{"time":601814,"text":"half an hour after his removal."}]},{"cues":[{"time":606450,"text":"Twenty-three years after apartheid,"},{"time":609234,"text":"a new generation of radicals\nhas arisen in South Africa."},{"time":612661,"text":"The story of Chapungu and Rhodes\nin the same space and time"},{"time":617558,"text":"asks important questions"},{"time":619337,"text":"related to gender,"},{"time":622236,"text":"power,"},{"time":623537,"text":"self-representation,"},{"time":625342,"text":"history making"},{"time":626955,"text":"and repatriation."},{"time":631250,"text":"From then on,"},{"time":632424,"text":"I realized that my spiritual\nbeliefs and dreams"},{"time":637669,"text":"texture my material reality."},{"time":641429,"text":"But for me, Chapungu's story\nfelt incomplete."},{"time":644816,"text":"This soapstone bird,"},{"time":646589,"text":"a spiritual medium and messenger\nof God and the ancestors,"},{"time":650980,"text":"needed me to continue her story."},{"time":653681,"text":"And so I dabbled in the dream space\na little bit more,"},{"time":658121,"text":"and this is how \"Falling\" was born."}]},{"cues":[{"time":667389,"text":"[A film by Sethembile Msezane]"}]},{"cues":[{"time":668880,"text":"(Video) (A capella singing)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":699989,"text":"[FALLING]"}]},{"cues":[{"time":706914,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":710751,"text":"In the film,"},{"time":711925,"text":"Zimbabwe, South Africa and Germany\nshare a common story"},{"time":715707,"text":"about the soapstone birds\nthat were looted from Great Zimbabwe."},{"time":720336,"text":"After Zimbabwe gained its independence,"},{"time":722673,"text":"all the birds except for one\nwere returned to the monument."},{"time":727164,"text":"\"Falling\" explores the mythological belief\nthat there will be unrest"},{"time":732314,"text":"until the final bird is returned."}]},{"cues":[{"time":736898,"text":"Through my work,"},{"time":738245,"text":"I have realized a lot\nabout the world around me:"},{"time":742237,"text":"how we move through spaces,"},{"time":745289,"text":"who we choose to celebrate"},{"time":747648,"text":"and who we remember."},{"time":750080,"text":"Now I look in the mirror\nand not only see an image of myself,"},{"time":754859,"text":"but of the women\nwho have made me who I am today."},{"time":758716,"text":"I stand tall in my work,"},{"time":761788,"text":"celebrating women's histories,"},{"time":764273,"text":"in the hope that perhaps one day,"},{"time":767494,"text":"no little black girl has to ever feel"},{"time":770774,"text":"like she doesn't exist."}]},{"cues":[{"time":772684,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":773928,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}